<ns120:section xmlns:ns120="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.persistence.rdbms.mysql.installation.simple">

  <ns121:title xmlns:ns121="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Installing MySQL</ns121:title>
  <ns122:para xmlns:ns122="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    MySQL is an open-source relational database which can
    be downloaded for a number of platforms from <ns123:literal xmlns:ns123="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">www.mysql.com</ns123:literal>.
  </ns122:para>
  <ns124:para xmlns:ns124="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    When accessing the database from Java you will have to download a JDBC driver .
    You may also want to download some GUI client for the database.
  </ns124:para>
  
  <ns125:section xmlns:ns125="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns126:title xmlns:ns126="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Installing the MySQL Database Server</ns126:title>
    <ns127:para xmlns:ns127="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      On Linux simply install the RPM distribution via
<ns128:programlisting xmlns:ns128="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
 rpm -i MySQL-version.rpm
</ns128:programlisting>    
    </ns127:para>
    <ns129:para xmlns:ns129="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      On Windows unzip the zip file and run <ns130:literal xmlns:ns130="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Setup.exe</ns130:literal>.
    </ns129:para>
  </ns125:section>
</ns120:section>